(firstQuint)Efficiency and Safety of Prophylactic Use of Antibiotics in Endoscopic Injection of Tissue Adhesive in Gastric Varices.

 At present, there is still a controversy about the application of antibiotics in the treatment of patients with non acute hemorrhage of esophageal varices.

 This study is a randomized controlled trial.

 Patients randomly enter two treatment groups: 1.

 the prophylactic use of antibiotics group and 2.

 the non-prophylactic use of antibiotics group Treatment allocation is by block randomization with an equal number for both groups.

 The incidence of infection after endoscopic treatment will be analyzed.

